-font-weight:theme;\">FAQs \u2013 Shopping Ads in Kenya<\/h2><\/div><\/div>[vc_tta_accordion][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Can Shopping Ads work for my Shopify store?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-shopify-1&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nYes. Shopify connects to Google Merchant Center through the official Google &amp; YouTube app, which syncs your catalogue automatically. We still optimise the feed in Merchant Center to improve search relevance. That includes tighter product titles, clearer descriptions, correct categories, image checks, and feed rules to fix missing or inconsistent data. We then link Merchant Center to Google Ads, confirm conversion tracking in GA4, and apply product segmentation so your budget favours bestsellers and higher-margin items.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;What is the difference between Standard Shopping and Smart Shopping (Performance Max)?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-std-smart-2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nStandard Shopping gives you granular control. You can segment by category or margin, set bids at product group level, and add negative keywords to cut waste. Performance Max automates placements across Search, Shopping, Display, YouTube, Discover, and Gmail, and uses data signals and conversion history to push for sales. Our default approach in Kenya is a hybrid. Keep high-value or seasonal products in Standard Shopping for precision and learning, and use Performance Max to expand reach once the feed and tracking are strong.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;How long does it take to see results?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-timing-3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nIf Merchant Center approves the feed quickly, expect traffic within 1 to 2 weeks. Algorithmic optimisation typically stabilises by weeks 4 to 6. Timelines depend on catalogue size, competition, and data quality. We front-load work on feed quality, conversion tracking, and campaign structure so early spend produces reliable signals. That shortens the path to profitable bids and clearer scaling decisions.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;What budget should I start with?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-budget-4&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nA practical starting range for Kenyan e-commerce is KES 50,000 to KES 100,000 per month. This funds testing across product groups and devices while gathering enough data for statistically sound decisions. If unit margins are thin or competition is high, begin at the lower end, protect margin with tighter segmentation, and scale once target ROAS is reached. We reallocate budget weekly to back proven products and reduce exposure on underperformers.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Can I run Shopping Ads if I sell internationally?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-international-5&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nYes. Configure additional target countries in Merchant Center, submit prices in the correct currency, and set country-specific shipping. Ensure language and policy pages meet local rules. We recommend separate campaigns or Performance Max asset groups per market so bids, creatives, and budgets align with local demand and competition. Inventory accuracy is critical when stock is shared across regions.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;What happens if my products get disapproved?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-disapprovals-6&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nDisapprovals usually come from missing attributes, price or availability mismatches, poor images, or policy issues. We monitor Merchant Center diagnostics daily, correct the feed with rules or attribute fixes, and align website data with feed values. If a policy error is incorrect, we submit an appeal with evidence. Preventative maintenance matters. Schema, consistent pricing, clear variants, and clean images reduce future disapprovals and keep impression share steady.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Can I advertise seasonal or limited-edition products?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-seasonal-7&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<br \/>\nYes. Create dedicated campaigns or product groups for seasonal or limited lines. Increase bids during peak demand and cap spend when stock runs low. Keep stock and availability current in the feed to avoid overselling. For short windows such as Black Friday or back to school, schedule feed fetches more frequently, refresh images and prices, and layer promotions to lift click-through and conversion rate.<br \/>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][\/vc_tta_accordion]<\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; type=&#8221;vc_default&#8221; margin_top=&#8221;5&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;10&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1716548610536{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_single_image image=&#8221;5996&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;center&#8221; css=&#8221;&#8221; lazy_loading=&#8221;true&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;] What Are Google Shopping Ads? Definition of Shopping Ads \/ Product Listing Ads (PLAs)Google Shopping Ads\u2014also known as Product Listing Ads (PLAs)\u2014are visually rich, product-focused adverts that display key product elements: image, title, price, store name, and ratings.&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":5996,"parent":47,"menu_order":10,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_mons